<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 5:20PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Glacier
County through 545 PM MDT...
At 520 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles northeast of West Glacier, or 41 miles northeast of Evergreen,
moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Many Glacier, Babb, Saint Mary and Logan Pass.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
